 `stepperActions` is initialized. This handles URL parsing and applies the stored data. Now, I will design a \"Copy Shareable Link\" button. I will start by examining the component's existing layout, specifically lines 930-1005, to determine where to integrate the new sharing option.\n\n\n**Designing Sharing Interface**\n\nI'm now designing the interface for sharing the blueprint summary. I've added a \"Copy Summary\" button that, on click, will copy the summary data to the clipboard. There's also a \"Save Locally\" button to save the data in the browser's local storage. I'm focusing on their placement and styling within the component, with careful consideration for the user experience.\n\n\n**Designing Sharing Interaction**\n\nI'm now thinking about adding a \"Copy Shareable Link\" button next to the \"Save to Edge\" and \"Print Report\" buttons. I'll need a new state variable, `isShared`, to track if the link was successfully copied. I'm focusing on the component's layout, specifically where to integrate this new feature, and how it should behave in relation to the existing buttons.\n\n\n**Implementing Sharing Feature**\n\nI've implemented the \"Copy Shareable Link\" functionality. The button, when clicked, serializes the blueprint data, creates a shareable URL with a \"blueprint\" parameter containing the encoded data, and copies the URL to the clipboard. I am using a try-catch block to handle potential errors and set the `isShared` state. It also includes a 2-second timeout to reset the `isShared` state.\n\n\n**Verifying Component Integration**\n\nI'm now verifying the \"Copy Shareable Link\" button integration within the `BlueprintGenerator.tsx` component. The added button includes SVG styling and text matching the existing color scheme, using a subtle purple accent. It's beautiful and consistent with our UI. I am reviewing the color changes and button states. Now I will thoroughly check its responsiveness and ensure it integrates seamlessly with the existing layout and user flow.\n\n\n"}}
